Drugged-up Carl Barlow drove on the wrong side of the road and went through red lights as he was chased by police. 
 
Officers had attempted to stop the 27-year-old&apos;s Toyota car after he sped off from traffic lights in Broad Street, Hanley, and turned into Sun Street. 
 
But Barlow took police on a seven-minute pursuit as he went the wrong way down a one-way street, went round a roundabout the wrong way, and drove through red lights. 
 
