The pursuit came to an end when Barlow was arrested after he misjudged a turning and ended up in a front garden within a cul-de-sac. 
 
The defendant failed to give a sample of blood and refused a drugs test at the police station. 
 
Now Barlow has been jailed for nine months and banned from driving for 28-and-a-half months following the July 10 offence. 
 
Prosecutor Heather Chamberlin told Stoke-on-Trent Crown Court: “The Toyota accelerated strongly in Broad Street and turned right into Sun Street. The officer illuminated his lights but the car failed to stop. 
 
