“It went the wrong way down a one-way street, went round a roundabout the wrong way and drove on the wrong side of Cobridge Road. It travelled at 60mph in a 30mph zone. He took a mini roundabout on the wrong side of the road and veered from side to side. He went through traffic lights on Festival Park on the wrong side of the road causing a vehicle to reverse out of the way. He went through various junctions without stopping. Eventually he misjudged a turning and ended up in a cul-de-sac and came to a stop on the grass of a front garden. 
 
“He was arrested. It was clear he was under the influence of some sort of intoxicant. He was searched and there was a psychoactive substance in his pocket, a legal high which is now illegal.&quot; 
 
The defendant tested &apos;zero&apos; for alcohol. He told police he had been smoking monkey dust and knew he would fail a drugs test so he refused to take one. 
 
