Barlow, of Davison Street, Cobridge, pleaded guilty to dangerous driving, driving without a licence, driving without insurance, failing to provide a specimen of blood, and refusing a drug test. 
 
Anis Ali, mitigating, said: “He acted out of stupidity. He realises what he did was dangerous. He recognises the potential for harm and injury being occasioned. He self-confessed he had been using illicit substances which explains why he failed to comply. He realises he can&apos;t carry on in the way he has been.&quot; 
 
Recorder Stephen Thomas told Barlow: “The seven-minute pursuit involved you driving at up to 60mph in a 30mph area. It involved you weaving around narrow streets with houses on either side and causing other vehicles to alter their course to accommodate you.&quot; 
 
